The paper discusses parallel batched data structures and their implementation in a parallel computing model. This topic falls under the category of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC). The paper also proposes a technique called parallel combining, which involves explicit synchronization of concurrent operations into batches. This technique can be applied to various data structures, including dynamic graphs and priority queues, which fall under the categories of Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) and Programming Languages (cs.PL). Additionally, the paper discusses the performance gains achieved by the proposed technique, which can be considered as a form of optimization (cs.PF). Finally, the paper's focus on parallel computing and synchronization can also be related to the category of Systems and Control (cs.SY).
